#Approach:

Find Minimum in Rotated Sorted Array – Binary Search Approach

Is problem me sorted array rotate ho chuki hoti hai,
aur hume minimum element find karna hota hai.

Observation:
Har step par array ka ek half definitely sorted hota hai.
Agar left half sorted hai, to us half ka minimum nums[low] hoga.
To hum ans ko nums[low] se update kar sakte hain
aur minimum dusre half me ho sakta hai, isliye right side me search karte hain.

Agar left half sorted nahi hai,
to iska matlab rotation point left half me hai
aur minimum nums[mid] ya uske left side me ho sakta hai.
Isliye ans ko nums[mid] se update karte hain
aur high = mid - 1 karke left side me search karte hain.

Is tarah har step par search space half hoti rehti hai,
isliye time complexity O(log n) rehti hai.

Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int findMin(int[] nums) {
        int low = 0;
        int high = nums.length-1;
        int ans = Integer.MAX_VALUE;

        while(low <= high){
            int mid = (low + high)/2;

            //if left half is sorted
            if(nums[low] <= nums[mid]){
                ans = Math.min(ans, nums[low]);
                low = mid+1;
            }
            //if right half is sorted
            else{
                ans = Math.min(ans, nums[mid]);
                high = mid-1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
